  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C" class="c1">Went down there tonight to grab the rod for my friends staff of the wheel quest and the jaw bone for the my Divine Might quest.  49 paladin here, he was a 40 wizard.  I had heard the horror stories about Miragul so we were very careful where we walked.  He accidently grabbed the jaw bone so as we were sitting around I noticed two skeletons wondering toward us and quickly clicked and had Lich of Miragul targeted.  We both had IVU up and he walked right over my friend.  I conned him, blue to me, the pet was blue as well.  My friend conned him and got blue as well(I believe he may have had the pet targeted though)  Being the ballsy type, we decided to give it a shot, so I went into it just as I would duelling a PC necro; SoWed up, and feared the pet then took off back around a corner so he couldn't cast on me.  After about a minate, my fear spell had worn off and the pet came over to harrass us, and he was dispatched very quickly.  I poked my head around the corner, and he didn't come back at all to knock it off.  So we sat back down to wait for the jaw bone to repop and IVUed up to avoid the dumb Ice-Bones that wonder through and hit ya if you're sitting.  After about 5 minates, I looked up to see the Lich of Miragul with a new pet baring down hard on us.  I went to target the pet to fear it(should've gone after Miragul himself) which left the Lich with an opening to fear me.  My God, his fear is ROUGH.  I've been feared by the best of em, Wuoshi, Draco, Naggy, mobs in Fear, and this was by far one of the worst fears that has ever hit me, especially from a blue.  He then proceded to basically fear-kite both myself and the wizard til we expired.  He hit pretty hard, 160's or so, but it was fairly slow when compared to SoV and RoK mobs.  His pet had little hit points and missed quite often.  I think we could've taken him if I kept him stunned between my DW bracers and spells, guess I'll just haveta wait til I kill Naggy and Vox til I get my revenge....<br><br></td></tr>
