  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#13273C" class="c1">I spent last weekend camping the Glacier Bear, and I have a few things to add here, as the Lich was up the whole time I was there.  One thing to note is that he looks just like a normal lvl 8 skeleton, so don't do like I did and walk up to him expecting to kill one of the IB placeholders...  You will tell him apart because he has a redish brown necro pet following him (pet was yellow to me at 34).  The Lich, the Glacier Bear, and the IB skeleton PHs for the bear are the only things that wander in the cave.  The Lich makes a circle around the cave every 15 minutes.  I do not know his complete path, but I do know this.  I waited on the northern wall of the cave in the tunnel leading to Sulon McMoor, where there is a slight widening of the tunnel running east/west, and I waited on the northern wall of this wide area and the Lich did not aggro on me while I waited there.  (For Shammies camping the bear, he will not aggro on your pet, even if the pet is attacking one of the IB skeles.  Imagine my heart drop when I saw the Lich walk right by my pet fighting an IB!  I expect that he will also not aggro on a player in wolf form, but this is just speculation on my part.)  Fom what I observed of his path, he walks into the room with Sulon, waits a min or two and then walks out along the northern hallway into the NE alcove with the large tomb structure, where he waits again for a few ticks.  Then he walks back west and turns south to go around the cave counterclockwise, eventually coming back to Sulon.  Entire round trip takes 15 minutes.  I do know that he goes into at least one of the southern alcoves, but I don't remember which one.  The northern alcove between Sulon and the NE alcove where the Lich wanders is safe.  This alcove has two stationary IB's and a small white tomb, and this is where I fought the Glacier Bear.  The IB's here won't usually aggro on you unless you get right in their face a lot.  BTW, http://www.eqshaman.com/guides/glacierbear.html has a decent map of the caves along with the paths of the bear and IB skeles.  The Lich roughly follows the red path marked on this map.  Spawn time for the bear was 7 hours instead of 8 hours like this guide says.  Good luck on avoiding/killing the Lich, whichever you came here to do.<br><br></td></tr>
